$ bash get_patric_genomes.sh

####################

Some comments to the function:
def get_patric_genomes(patric_ids_file, save_directory):
    '''Needs a file with patric_ids of interest and a saving directory. Downloads the genomes (fna files)
    of the ids.'''

Avoid making this a python function to download the genomes. Instead make it a function that writes a bash script to download the genomes.
The reason is that likely it will take python forever to download 12000 genomes with os.system.


